$interpreted: : One month later...
Yang-Tai: *Cough* *cough*... How can I afford to repay... this month...
Hoodlum: Hey! Where are you, gramps? It's payday!
Hoodlum: So this is where you're hiding, huh?
Yang-Tai: I'm not *cough*... *cough*... I'm not trying to hide...
Hoodlum: You won't fool anyone with a couple of coughs. Time for you to pay up on this month's interest!
Yang-Tai: I'm sorry... *cough* I don't have it right now...
Hoodlum: Again?! And you don't even have an excuse, huh. All right, smash it up!
Puzzled Punk: Uhh... There's nothing left to smash, boss...
Hoodlum: You've got to repay your debts somehow, gramps. All right, you'll just have to smash HIM up until he coughs up the interest!
Baa Baa: Wait!
Baa Baa: Can't we talk this over? Ya needn't use your fists first.
Hoodlum: Who d'you think you are? I hate it when anyone interrupts my raging!
Baa Baa: Here's a little something for your troubles. Please, give the man a break.
Hoodlum: Hmph, don't make me ask twice next time.
Yang-Tai: *cough* Baa Baa! You're back...? *cough*...
Baa Baa: ...You don't look so good...
Yang-Tai: I'm fine. It's just good to see you again.
Yang-Tai: But where did you get all that money?
Baa Baa: Well... I helped the Alliance to track down the thief who stole their cash, and they rewarded me for it.
Yang-Tai: So that's where you went... I've caused you so much trouble.
Baa Baa: Not at all, President.
Yang-Tai: And you're still calling me President, too...
Yang-Tai: All right... I'm getting ready to visit a friend. You should come with me, *cough*...
Baa Baa: You should rest, President.
Yang-Tai: I won't be able to rest until I've seen to this. Let's go.
Yang-Tai: Long time no see, how have you been?
Demihuman Merchant: President Yang-Tai... I've been... okay, I guess.
Yang-Tai: I see. Actually, I came to ask you a favor.
Demihuman Merchant: Whatever it is, just say the word, and I'll do all I can to help.
Yang-Tai: Well, I just need a little cash flow, if it's not too much to ask.
Demihuman Merchant: Oh, I... I'm really sorry, Yang-Tai. You've seen how expensive things are getting, and I'm having trouble making ends meet myself...
Yang-Tai: Please, I'm the one who should be sorry.
Demihuman Merchant: Next time! Next time, I promise I'll help you!
Former Aid Recipient: Ahh, I wish I could help... but... I've got a kid on the way, and you know how much it costs to raise a child... Healthcare, education, all that...
Former Aid Recipient: Ah... This is really unfortunate, I've just gotten engaged... and I can't make any big financial decisions by myself now...
Yang-Tai: Oh, I see... *cough*... *cough* *cough*... Let's try somewhere else.
Baa Baa: Forget it, President. Can't ya see? That's just how people are. They turn into animals at the mere mention of money.
Baa Baa: Anyone who coulda helped woulda stepped in by now.
Yang-Tai: Don't talk nonsense... *cough*... It's just that... *cough*... everybody's in hard times right now...
Baa Baa: President! President?!
Baa Baa: Will he be all right, Doc?
Doctor: He's suffered a stroke from overwork and exhaustion. He's been paralyzed.
Baa Baa: But... but...
Baa Baa: How can we cure him? How much do you want?
Doctor: Sigh... It's not a question of money. I'm afraid this is just how it'll be for him now. I'm sorry, please take care.
Baa Baa: ...I knew he should have gotten out while he could... This would never have happened...
Sennosuke: So, the rumors are true. The old man's paralyzed.
Sennosuke: How very, very interesting.
Sennosuke: Here! Come get your reward. You've done well over the past two years.
Sennosuke: See, isn't this your favorite little girl? How do you think she was getting by all this time?
Baa Baa: ...You can see the state he's in already, don't make things even harder for him.
Sennosuke: Oh, feeling sympathetic, are we? Well, you always were his little girl, he never tried to hide it.
Baa Baa: That's not true~ He needed help, so... we were just helping each other out.
Sennosuke: Heheh, it's all the same to me. You and him both sold Yang-Tai out.
Baa Baa: Papa Gu?!
Sennosuke: This old geezer came running to me the moment he saw signs of trouble.
Papa Gu: That muddled fool was too big for his boots. I was just getting my money back.
Sennosuke: Shut it! Who said you could speak? I'll put you in the ground if cut in again.
Papa Gu: Okay, okay.
Baa Baa: ......
Baa Baa: (I knew it, you can't trust anyone...)
Baa Baa: (Even I... can't be trusted...)
Sennosuke: Finally, I've got some good news. As agreed in our contract, everything, including you, now belongs to me. Bwahaha~
Baa Baa: You won't get anywhere by trusting in people.
Sennosuke: That's right. I've got even better jobs lined up for you.
Baa Baa: I hope you'll take care of me... Let me pay off the rest of the President's debts for him.
Baa Baa: (Huh? What am I saying...)
Papa Gu: Are you crazy...? Baa Baa!
Sennosuke: Hey! Quit joking around. Enough of this second-rate goody-goody act.
Baa Baa: I'm not~ I'm serious.
Baa Baa: (Really...? Why... Why would I do such a thing...)
Sennosuke: ...Listen, kid. You'd better think carefully. This isn't something you can just talk the talk on without walking the walk, too.
Baa Baa: (I...)
Baa Baa: （……）
Baa Baa: （…………）
Baa Baa: He's my Pops. I'll pay his debts.
Baa Baa: Ya can call me Yang Baa Baa from now. Doesn't the name suit me? This way you can earn a little extra through the interest payments, too.
Sennosuke: Fine. I don't know if you're crazy or what, but what do I care—money is money.
Baa Baa: Wonderful, Papa Gu! I'll be glad to see ya again soon~
Papa Gu: What's the matter with this kid? That laughter's giving me the heebie-jeebies...
Baa Baa: I always said ya can't trust anybody. In the end, money's the only thing anybody believes in.
Baa Baa: I'm sorry, Pops. I'll help you pay everything back~
Baa Baa: Until then, you'll do everything I say, won't cha?
Yang-Tai: ...Baa...Baa...
